Package projectmanager

Class Person

java.lang.Object
projectmanager.Person
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Person
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
This class defines a Person object.

It is used by ProjectManager, and implements Serializable interface.

Changes from V1: code refactored, attributes encapsulated, instances now writable to file, and updatePerson method moved to ProjectManager.

Changes from V2.0: Methods selectPerson and updatePerson moved here from ProjectManager. Method populatePersonsMap added.

Version:
V2.1 August 2021

      Creates a Person.
      Parameters:
      type - a String containing "Architect", "Contractor", or "Customer"
      surname - a String containing the person's surname
      name - a String containing the person's first name
      cellNum - a String containing the person's cell number
      emailAddress - a String containing the person's email address
      physAddress - a String containing the person's residential address

    • selectPerson

      public static Person selectPerson​(java.lang.String name, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​Person> map)
      Iterates through a Map containing Person objects, selects a Person according to the parameter, and then displays and returns the selected Person.
      Parameters:
      name - a String containing the name and/or surname of a Person
      map - a Map with String keys and Person values
      Returns:
      the selected Person object (null if no project found)
      Since:
      V1

    • updatePerson

      public void updatePerson​(java.lang.String[] personInfo)
      Updates Person contact-detail attributes (cellNum, emailAddress, and physAddress).

      Takes an Array containing the details as parameter. If details were left blank, the attributes remain unchanged.

      Changes from V1: moved from Person class, user input validation added.

      Parameters:
      personInfo - a String Array containing new attribute values.
      Since:
      V1
